---
target: editor
version: 1
validations:
  - name: editor-module-exists
    type: folder_check
    path: src/editor

  - name: editor-static-assets-exist
    type: folder_check
    path: src/editor/static
    children: [index.html, styles.css]

  - name: editor-server-structure
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify the editor server module:
      1. Defines a function or class to start an HTTP server on a configurable port
      2. Serves static files (HTML, JS, CSS) for the frontend
      3. Registers REST API routes for DAG, targets, specs, validations, project, and status
      4. Registers WebSocket endpoints for file-change notifications and agent interaction
      5. Accepts a project path and validates it is an initialized intentc project
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/editor/**"]

  - name: editor-api-endpoints
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify the editor API module implements:
      1. GET endpoint returning the full DAG structure (nodes, edges, statuses)
      2. GET endpoint returning a specific target's spec content and validations
      3. PUT endpoint that writes updated spec content to the target's .ic file on disk
      4. PUT endpoint that writes updated validation content to the target's .icv file on disk
      5. GET endpoint returning the project-level intent (project.ic)
      6. GET endpoint returning build status for all targets
      7. All reads come from files on disk (no in-memory cache as source of truth)
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/editor/**"]

  - name: editor-file-watcher
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify the editor includes a file watcher that:
      1. Watches the intent/ directory for file changes (create, modify, delete)
      2. Emits change events when .ic or .icv files are modified
      3. Integrates with a WebSocket or streaming mechanism to push updates to connected clients
      4. Handles external changes (files edited outside the editor or by agents)
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/editor/**"]

  - name: editor-agent-bridge
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify the editor agent bridge:
      1. Accepts a prompt and target name from the client
      2. Loads the target's spec (.ic) and validations (.icv) to construct context
      3. Resolves and uses the project's configured agent profile from .intentc/config.yaml
      4. Invokes the agent and streams output back to the client incrementally
      5. Uses the agent module's CreateFromProfile or equivalent factory
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/editor/**"]

  - name: editor-dag-visualization
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify the frontend DAG visualization:
      1. Renders nodes as boxes connected by directional arrows
      2. Flows top to bottom (root nodes at top, leaves at bottom)
      3. Each node displays the target name and a build status indicator
      4. Clicking a node triggers selection (updates the center pane)
      5. DAG data is fetched from the server API
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/editor/static/**"]

  - name: editor-spec-editing
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify the frontend spec/validation editor:
      1. Displays the selected target's .ic file content in an editable text area
      2. Displays each .icv file in its own editable text area
      3. Saves changes to disk via the server API (PUT endpoints)
      4. Shows the target's build status and latest build result
      5. Auto-refreshes when file-change notifications arrive via WebSocket
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/editor/static/**"]

  - name: editor-agent-chat
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify the frontend agent chat:
      1. Provides a message input and send action
      2. Sends prompts to the server with the currently selected target name
      3. Displays agent responses with streaming (incremental rendering)
      4. Maintains conversation history within the session
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/editor/static/**"]

  - name: editor-cli-command
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify the CLI integration:
      1. An 'edit' command is registered in the CLI
      2. Accepts a project path argument
      3. Accepts an optional --port flag (default 8080)
      4. Validates the project path is an initialized intentc project
      5. Starts the editor server and prints the URL
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/cli/**", "src/editor/**"]

  - name: editor-three-pane-layout
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify the frontend layout:
      1. Three-pane layout: left (DAG), center (editor), right (agent chat)
      2. All three panes are visible simultaneously
      3. Layout is responsive or uses reasonable fixed proportions
      4. Panes are visually distinct with clear boundaries
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/editor/static/**"]

  - name: editor-tests-pass
    type: command_check
    command: cd src && uv run pytest editor/ -v
    exit_code: 0
---

# Editor Validations

The editor is the terminal feature of intentc, integrating the CLI, DAG, parser, state, and agent modules into an interactive web-based environment. Validations cover the server, API, file watcher, agent bridge, frontend visualization, editing, chat, and CLI integration. Tests should mock the agent and file system interactions for speed and determinism.
